				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Turn for the Wurst" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Get your buns warmed up for this hotdog building game! Players compete to acquire ingredients, complete recipes, and score points in this rummy style card game. Don't worry if you find yourself in a pickle, there are plenty of rounds to play and earn your cheese. Have fun chilli-n with your friends and don't stress you'll have plenty of time to ketchup on points, and we hope this game doesn't leave you feeling Sauer(kraut)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn for the wurst uses a tongue in cheek art style to flavor this rummy style recipe completion card game. Players begin the game with seven condiment cards and three recipe (goal) cards. On their turn players may do one of the following...&amp;#10;1. Draw two cards off the deck then discard one condiment card.&amp;#10;2. Dig a card from the discard pile, keeping every card on top of it, then discard a condiment card.&amp;#10;3. Draw two recipe cards keeping one and placing one in the community recipe pile.&amp;#10;4. Claim a recipe card from the community pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players may complete a recipe card from their hand or play a set (3 of a kind) of condiment cards at anytime to score points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A round ends when one player has finished at least three recipe cards and discarded their last card OR &amp;quot;Knockwursts&amp;quot;, similar to knocking in gin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a round ends all players tally up their score from that round. A full game is played until a player has reached 100 total points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
